On Thu, 12 Jun 1997 09:32:10 +0200 Luc ALBERT 
<albert@cal.enst.fr> wrote:

> Is is possible in Caml Light to  automatically produce  ps files ?

There are actually two interfaces to PostScript I know: 

The MLgraph system on

 ftp://ftp.ens.fr/pub/unix/lang/MLgraph/

provides a direct way to produce PostScript images from 
within Caml Light or OCaml.

With the CamlTK interface located in

  ftp://ftp.inria.fr/lang/caml-light/camltk/

you can draw an image on a TK Canvas widget and then export 
this image as Encapsulated PostScript.

- Jens 

